"time over the SMB protocol (ports 445 or 139).\n"
"This is done by starting a session with the anonymous\n"
"account (or with a proper user account, if one is given; it likely doesn't make\n"
"a difference); in response to a session starting, the server will send back all this\n"
"information."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Attempts to print text on a shared printer by calling Print Spooler Service "
"RPC functions."
msgstr ""

msgid "Attempts to list the supported protocols and dialects of a SMB server."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Implements remote process execution similar to the Sysinternals' psexec\n"
"tool, allowing a user to run a series of programs on a remote machine and\n"
"read the output. This is great for gathering information about servers,\n"
"running the same tool on a range of system, or even installing a backdoor on\n"
"a collection of computers."
msgstr ""

msgid "Returns information about the SMB security level determined by SMB."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Attempts to grab the server's statistics over SMB and MSRPC, which uses TCP\n"
"ports 445 or 139."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Pulls back information about the remote system from the registry. Getting all\n"
"of the information requires an administrative account, although a user account\n"
"will still get a lot of it. Guest probably won't get any, nor will anonymous.\n"
"This goes for all operating systems, including Windows 2000."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Detects Microsoft Windows systems infected by the Conficker worm. This check is dangerous and\n"
"it may crash systems."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Checks if target machines are vulnerable to the arbitrary shared library load\n"
"vulnerability CVE-2017-7494."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Detects Microsoft Windows systems vulnerable to denial of service (CVE-2009-3103).\n"
"This script will crash the service if it is vulnerable."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Detects Microsoft Windows systems with Ras RPC service vulnerable to "
"MS06-025."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Detects Microsoft Windows systems with Dns Server RPC vulnerable to "
"MS07-029."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Detects Microsoft Windows systems vulnerable to the remote code execution vulnerability\n"
"known as MS08-067. This check is dangerous and it may crash systems."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Tests whether target machines are vulnerable to the ms10-054 SMB remote memory\n"
"corruption vulnerability."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Tests whether target machines are vulnerable to ms10-061 Printer Spooler "
"impersonation vulnerability."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Attempts to detect if a Microsoft SMBv1 server is vulnerable to a remote code\n"
"execution vulnerability (ms17-010, a.k.a. EternalBlue).\n"
"The vulnerability is actively exploited by WannaCry and Petya ransomware and other malware."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Checks if a Microsoft Windows 2000 system is vulnerable to a crash in regsvc caused by a null pointer\n"
"dereference. This check will crash the service if it is vulnerable and requires a guest account or\n"
"higher to work."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Checks whether the WebExService is installed and allows us to run code."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Attempts to run a command via WebExService, using the WebExec vulnerability.\n"
"Given a Windows account (local or domain), this will start an arbitrary\n"
"executable with SYSTEM privileges over the SMB protocol."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Attempts to list the supported capabilities in a SMBv2 server for each\n"
"enabled dialect."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Determines the message signing configuration in SMBv2 servers\n"
"for all supported dialects."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Attempts to obtain the current system date and the start date of a SMB2 "
"server."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Attempts to detect missing patches in Windows systems by checking the\n"
"uptime returned during the SMB2 protocol negotiation."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Performs brute force password auditing against SMTP servers using either "
"LOGIN, PLAIN, CRAM-MD5, DIGEST-MD5 or NTLM authentication."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Attempts to use EHLO and HELP to gather the Extended commands supported by an\n"
"SMTP server."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Attempts to enumerate the users on a SMTP server by issuing the VRFY, EXPN or RCPT TO\n"
"commands. The goal of this script is to discover all the user accounts in the remote\n"
"system."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"This script enumerates information from remote SMTP services with NTLM\n"
"authentication enabled."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Attempts to relay mail by issuing a predefined combination of SMTP commands. The goal\n"
"of this script is to tell if a SMTP server is vulnerable to mail relaying."
msgstr ""

msgid "Checks if SMTP is running on a non-standard port."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Checks for and/or exploits a heap overflow within versions of Exim\n"
"prior to version 4.69 (CVE-2010-4344) and a privilege escalation\n"
"vulnerability in Exim 4.72 and prior (CVE-2010-4345)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Checks for a memory corruption in the Postfix SMTP server when it uses\n"
"Cyrus SASL library authentication mechanisms (CVE-2011-1720).  This\n"
"vulnerability can allow denial of service and possibly remote code\n"
"execution."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Checks for a format string vulnerability in the Exim SMTP server\n"
"(version 4.70 through 4.75) with DomainKeys Identified Mail (DKIM) support\n"
"(CVE-2011-1764).  The DKIM logging mechanism did not use format string\n"
"specifiers when logging some parts of the DKIM-Signature header field.\n"
"A remote attacker who is able to send emails, can exploit this vulnerability\n"
"and execute arbitrary code with the privileges of the Exim daemon."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Checks if a target on a local Ethernet has its network card in promiscuous "
"mode."
msgstr ""

msgid "Attempts to find an SNMP community string by brute force guessing."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Attempts to enumerate Huawei / HP/H3C Locally Defined Users through the\n"
"hh3c-user.mib OID"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Extracts basic information from an SNMPv3 GET request. The same probe is used\n"
"here as in the service version detection scan."
msgstr ""

msgid "Attempts to enumerate network interfaces through SNMP."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Attempts to downloads Cisco router IOS configuration files using SNMP RW "
"(v1) and display or save them."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Attempts to query SNMP for a netstat like output. The script can be used to\n"
"identify and automatically add new targets to the scan by supplying the\n"
"newtargets script argument."
msgstr ""

msgid "Attempts to enumerate running processes through SNMP."
msgstr ""

msgid "Attempts to extract system information from an SNMP service."
msgstr ""

msgid "Attempts to enumerate Windows services through SNMP."
msgstr ""

msgid "Attempts to enumerate Windows Shares through SNMP."
msgstr ""

msgid "Attempts to enumerate installed software through SNMP."
msgstr ""

msgid "Attempts to enumerate Windows user accounts through SNMP"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Determines the supported authentication mechanisms of a remote SOCKS\n"
"proxy server.  Starting with SOCKS version 5 socks servers may support\n"
"authentication.  The script checks for the following authentication\n"
"types:\n"
"0 - No authentication\n"
"1 - GSSAPI\n"
"2 - Username and password"
msgstr ""

msgid "Performs brute force password auditing against SOCKS 5 proxy servers."
msgstr ""

msgid "Checks if an open socks proxy is running on the target."
msgstr ""

msgid "Returns authentication methods that a SSH server supports."
msgstr ""

msgid "Performs brute-force password guessing against ssh servers."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"This script takes a table of paths to private keys, passphrases, and usernames\n"
"and checks each pair to see if the target ssh server accepts them for publickey\n"
"authentication. If no keys are given or the known-bad option is given, the\n"
"script will check if a list of known static public keys are accepted for\n"
"authentication."
msgstr ""

msgid "Runs remote command on ssh server and returns command output."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Reports the number of algorithms (for encryption, compression, etc.) that\n"
"the target SSH2 server offers. If verbosity is set, the offered algorithms\n"
"are each listed by type."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Checks if an SSH server supports the obsolete and less secure SSH Protocol "
"Version 1."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Detects whether a server is vulnerable to the SSL/TLS \"CCS Injection\"\n"
"vulnerability (CVE-2014-0224), first discovered by Masashi Kikuchi.\n"
"The script is based on the ccsinjection.c code authored by Ramon de C Valle\n"
"(https://gist.github.com/rcvalle/71f4b027d61a78c42607)"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Retrieves a server's SSL certificate. The amount of information printed about\n"
"the certificate depends on the verbosity level. With no extra verbosity, the\n"
"script prints the validity period and the commonName, organizationName,\n"
"stateOrProvinceName, and countryName of the subject. When present, it also\n"
"outputs all the subject alternative names."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Reports any private (RFC1918) IPv4 addresses found in the various fields of\n"
"an SSL service's certificate.  These will only be reported if the target\n"
"address itself is not private.  Nmap v7.30 or later is required."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Retrieves a target host's time and date from its TLS ServerHello response."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Weak ephemeral Diffie-Hellman parameter detection for SSL/TLS services."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"This script repeatedly initiates SSLv3/TLS connections, each time trying a new\n"
"cipher or compressor while recording whether a host accepts or rejects it. The\n"
"end result is a list of all the ciphersuites and compressors that a server accepts."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Detects whether a server is vulnerable to the OpenSSL Heartbleed bug (CVE-2014-0160).\n"
"The code is based on the Python script ssltest.py authored by Katie Stafford (katie@ktpanda.org)"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Checks whether the SSL certificate used by a host has a fingerprint\n"
"that matches an included database of problematic keys."
msgstr ""

msgid "Checks whether SSLv3 CBC ciphers are allowed (POODLE)"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Determines whether the server supports obsolete and less secure SSLv2, and discovers which ciphers it\n"
"supports."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Determines whether the server supports SSLv2, what ciphers it supports and tests for\n"
"CVE-2015-3197, CVE-2016-0703 and CVE-2016-0800 (DROWN)"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Check if the Secure Socket Tunneling Protocol is supported. This is\n"
"accomplished by trying to establish the HTTPS layer which is used to\n"
"carry SSTP traffic as described in:\n"
"- http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/cc247364.aspx"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Retrieves the external IP address of a NAT:ed host using the STUN protocol."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Sends a binding request to the server and attempts to extract version\n"
"information from the response, if the server attribute is present."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Detects whether a host is infected with the Stuxnet worm "
"(http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stuxnet)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Attempts to download an unprotected configuration file containing plain-text\n"
"user credentials in vulnerable Supermicro Onboard IPMI controllers."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Performs brute force password auditing against Subversion source code "
"control servers."
msgstr ""

msgid "Produces a list of IP prefixes for a given routing AS number (ASN)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"This script runs in the pre-scanning phase to convert 48-bit MAC addresses to\n"
"EUI-64 IPv6 addresses, which are often used for auto-configuration. Generated\n"
"addresses may be added to the scan queue."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"This script runs in the pre-scanning phase to map IPv4 addresses onto IPv6\n"
"networks and add them to the scan queue."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Sends an ICMPv6 echo request packet to the all-nodes link-local\n"
"multicast address (<code>ff02::1</code>) to discover responsive hosts\n"
"on a LAN without needing to individually ping each IPv6 address."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Sends an ICMPv6 packet with an invalid extension header to the\n"
"all-nodes link-local multicast address (<code>ff02::1</code>) to\n"
"discover (some) available hosts on the LAN. This works because some\n"
"hosts will respond to this probe with an ICMPv6 Parameter Problem\n"
"packet."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Attempts to discover available IPv6 hosts on the LAN by sending an MLD\n"
"(multicast listener discovery) query to the link-local multicast address\n"
"(ff02::1) and listening for any responses.  The query's maximum response delay\n"
"set to 1 to provoke hosts to respond immediately rather than waiting for other\n"
"responses from their multicast group."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Performs IPv6 host discovery by triggering stateless address auto-configuration\n"
"(SLAAC)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Adds IPv6 addresses to the scan queue using a wordlist of hexadecimal \"words\"\n"
"that form addresses in a given subnet."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Sniffs the local network for a configurable amount of time (10 seconds\n"
"by default) and prints discovered addresses. If the\n"
"<code>newtargets</code> script argument is set, discovered addresses\n"
"are added to the scan queue."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Inserts traceroute hops into the Nmap scanning queue. It only functions if\n"
"Nmap's <code>--traceroute</code> option is used and the <code>newtargets</code>\n"
"script argument is given."
msgstr ""

msgid "Loads addresses from an Nmap XML output file for scanning."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Detects the TeamSpeak 2 voice communication server and attempts to determine\n"
"version and configuration information."
msgstr ""

msgid "Performs brute-force password auditing against telnet servers."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Determines whether the encryption option is supported on a remote telnet\n"
"server.  Some systems (including FreeBSD and the krb5 telnetd available in many\n"
"Linux distributions) implement this option incorrectly, leading to a remote\n"
"root vulnerability. This script currently only tests whether encryption is\n"
"supported, not for that particular vulnerability."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"This script enumerates information from remote Microsoft Telnet services with NTLM\n"
"authentication enabled."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Enumerates TFTP (trivial file transfer protocol) filenames by testing\n"
"for a list of common ones."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Obtains information (such as vendor and device type where available) from a\n"
"TFTP service by requesting a random filename. Software vendor information is\n"
"determined by matching the error message against a database of known software."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Enumerates a TLS server's supported application-layer protocols using the "
"ALPN protocol."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Enumerates a TLS server's supported protocols by using the next protocol\n"
"negotiation extension."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Detects whether a server is vulnerable to the F5 Ticketbleed bug "
"(CVE-2016-9244)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Connects to a tn3270 'server' and returns the screen."
msgstr ""

msgid "Checks if a target is a known Tor node."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Lists the geographic locations of each hop in a traceroute and optionally\n"
"saves the results to a KML file, plottable on Google earth and maps."
msgstr ""

msgid "TSO account brute forcer."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"TSO User ID enumerator for IBM mainframes (z/OS). The TSO logon panel\n"
"tells you when a user ID is valid or invalid with the message:\n"
"<code>IKJ56420I Userid <user ID> not authorized to use TSO</code>."
msgstr ""

msgid "Extracts information from Ubiquiti networking devices."
msgstr ""

msgid "Runs unit tests on all NSE libraries."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Compares the detected service on a port against the expected service for that\n"
"port number (e.g. ssh on 22, http on 80) and reports deviations. The script\n"
"requires that a version scan has been run in order to be able to discover what\n"
"service is actually running on each port."
msgstr ""

msgid "Attempts to extract system information from the UPnP service."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Gets system information from an Idera Uptime Infrastructure Monitor agent."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Sniffs an interface for HTTP traffic and dumps any URLs, and their\n"
"originating IP address. Script output differs from other script as\n"
"URLs are written to stdout directly. There is also an option to log\n"
"the results to file."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Detects the Ventrilo voice communication server service versions 2.1.2\n"
"and above and tries to determine version and configuration\n"
"information. Some of the older versions (pre 3.0.0) may not have the\n"
"UDP service that this probe relies on enabled by default."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Extracts information, including file paths, version and database names from\n"
"a Versant object database."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Performs brute force password auditing against the VMWare Authentication "
"Daemon (vmware-authd)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Queries VMware server (vCenter, ESX, ESXi) SOAP API to extract the version "
"information."
msgstr ""

msgid "Performs brute force password auditing against VNC servers."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Queries a VNC server for its protocol version and supported security types."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Tries to log into a VNC server and get its desktop name. Uses credentials\n"
"discovered by vnc-brute, or None authentication types. If\n"
"<code>realvnc-auth-bypass</code> was run and returned VULNERABLE, this script\n"
"will use that vulnerability to bypass authentication."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Retrieves cluster and store information from the Voldemort distributed key-"
"value store using the Voldemort Native Protocol."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Many mainframes use VTAM screens to connect to various applications\n"
"(CICS, IMS, TSO, and many more)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"For each available CPE the script prints out known vulns (links to the "
"correspondent info) and correspondent CVSS scores."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Retrieves some basic information, including protocol version from a Vuze "
"filesharing node."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Detects vulnerabilities and gathers information (such as version\n"
"numbers and hardware support) from VxWorks Wind DeBug agents."
msgstr ""

msgid "Detect the T3 RMI protocol and Weblogic version"
msgstr ""

msgid "Attempts to retrieve information about the domain name of the target"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Queries the WHOIS services of Regional Internet Registries (RIR) and attempts to retrieve information about the IP Address\n"
"Assignment which contains the Target IP Address."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Retrieves and displays information from devices supporting the Web\n"
"Services Dynamic Discovery (WS-Discovery) protocol. It also attempts\n"
"to locate any published Windows Communication Framework (WCF) web\n"
"services (.NET 4.0 or later)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Checks if you're allowed to connect to the X server."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Requests an XDMCP (X display manager control protocol) session and lists "
"supported authentication and authorization mechanisms."
msgstr ""

msgid "Performs XMLRPC Introspection via the system.listMethods method."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Performs brute force password auditing against XMPP (Jabber) instant "
"messaging servers."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Connects to XMPP server (port 5222) and collects server information such as:\n"
"supported auth mechanisms, compression methods, whether TLS is supported\n"
"and mandatory, stream management, language, support of In-Band registration,\n"
"server capabilities.  If possible, studies server vendor."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Maps a WAN port on the router to a local port on the client using the NAT Port Mapping Protocol (NAT-PMP).  It supports the following operations:\n"
"* map - maps a new external port on the router to an internal port of the requesting IP\n"
"* unmap - unmaps a previously mapped port for the requesting IP\n"
"* unmapall - unmaps all previously mapped ports for the requesting IP"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"NOTE: This script has been replaced by the <code>--resolve-all</code>\n"
"command-line option in Nmap 7.70"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Queries Shodan API for given targets and produces similar output to\n"
"a -sV nmap scan. The ShodanAPI key can be set with the 'apikey' script\n"
"argument, or hardcoded in the .nse file itself. You can get a free key from"
msgstr ""

